  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">MD-Sketch-Element-Spline</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Popup Box"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:2px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:164px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><image src="MD-Sketch-Element-Spline.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:268px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">A </text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Spline</text> is a <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Sketch-Elements">sketch-element</link>. It is defined by the position, gradient, curvature of constraint points along the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Spline</text> shape.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The Spline can be open<image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image> or closed<image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image><text styleclass="Image Caption">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">If you click a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Spline</text> one time, then handles show<image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image>. You can drag the arrow-heads to control the gradient and the curvature of the spline at the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">You can drag the &apos;handles&apos; in the Mechanism-Editor and Part-Editors.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-FunctionBlock-BlendCurve">Blend-Curve</link>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
